parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck throttle plate or idle plate can cause the vehicle to accelerate erratically or not at all, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate when the accelerator pedal is pressed
the accelerator pedal sticks at various positions
the vehicle moves very slowly
the throttle plate or idle plate becomes stuck at idle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to slow down or stop unexpectedly, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a hissing sound
the brakes are slow to respond
the brakes fail to engage
the vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective vacuum booster pump can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a hissing sound
the brakes are slow to respond
the brakes fail to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with the brake design or specifications can cause braking problems, including reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brakes are slow to respond
the brakes fail to engage
the brake pads wear out prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The persistent idle instability can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine idles rough
the engine stalls frequently
the vehicle quits during normal operation
the vehicle hesitates or stutters when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel system malfunction can cause the engine to flood, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic. The stuck accelerator pedal can also cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control.
symptoms: The engine floods
the accelerator pedal is hard to press or sticks
the vehicle hesitates or stutters when accelerating
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly.
